Subject: [PATCH] feat(wallet): Add BTC and Tron address support to walletaccess intent

This patch adds support for requesting Bitcoin and Tron wallet addresses
through the walletaccess intent, enabling third-party apps to request
these addresses alongside ELA mainchain and ESC addresses.

## Motivation

Third-party applications like PC2 (Personal Cloud 2) need to display
multi-chain wallet balances for users who tether their Elastos DID.
Currently, the walletaccess intent only supports:
- elaaddress (ELA mainchain)
- elaamount (ELA balance)
- ethaddress (Elastos Smart Chain)

This leaves Bitcoin and Tron addresses inaccessible through the intent
system, even though Essentials already manages these wallets internally.

## Changes

1. `access.page.ts`: Add `btcaddress` and `tronaddress` cases to
   `getClaimValue()` and `getClaimTitle()` methods
2. Add translation keys for the new address types

## Usage

After this change, apps can request:
```javascript
{
  elaaddress: true,
  ethaddress: true,
  btcaddress: true,    // NEW
  tronaddress: true    // NEW
}
```

